  "text": "This study examined the effects of propofol on HeLa human cervical cancer cells. The major findings of this study were that propofol exerts antitumor effects by impairing autophagic flux, which involves induction of ER stress and regulation of AMPK/mTOR signaling. Propofol has recently been shown to reduce tumor size and weight [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This was confirmed in our study by the observation that HeLa cell viability was reduced by propofol treatment.",
